# Execution (`apply`, `loop`, implementation slices)

Canonical procedures: `.agents/workflows/sdd-apply.md`, `.agents/workflows/sdd-loop.md`, and `.agents/skills/sdd-apply/SKILL.md`.

## Slices

- Take **one** clear slice or `[AFK]` task per unattended iteration unless worktrees or ownership allow parallel lanes.
- Stop on ambiguity, missing acceptance criteria, or unresolved `[HITL]` blockers.

## TDD

For behavioral changes, default to **RED → GREEN → REFACTOR** when the project supports automated tests — see `skillgrid-tdd` skill when invoked. Never delete or weaken tests to force green.

## Evidence

Implementation is not complete until verification evidence exists: commands run, logs captured, paths referenced in handoff or envelope `artifacts`.

## After edits

Honor two-stage review (spec compliance then quality) before treating the slice as done. Critical findings block progression — see `.agents/rules/skillgrid-sdd-enforcement.mdc`.
